          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>Single parchment folio, Shelfmark: M.2002.1.385; Qurʾānic Text: 7:38-45; Lines per page: 16; Dimensions: 210 x 260 mm; Script style: kūfī type B.Ib; Estimated date of production: 750-900. The website of <ref target="https://collections.lacma.org/node/204558">Los Angeles County Museum has the following information about this fragment (consulted June 16th, 2021):</ref> "Page from a Manuscript of the Qur'an (7:38-45; 7:45-54), Arabia, Hijaz, second half of 8th-early 9th century, Manuscripts; folios, Ink on parchment, Folio, overall: 8 1/4 x 10 1/4 in. (20.96 x 26.04 cm); Text block: 7 3/16 x 8 3/4 in. (18.26 x 22.23 cm), The Madina Collection of Islamic Art, gift of Camilla Chandler Frost (M.2002.1.385), Art of the Middle East: Islamic and Contempory." Only an image of one side of the fragment is currently available which is labeled "fol. 1r" for technical reasons. For a detailed description of fragments of this early Qurʾān and a list of sister fragments in the collections of Gotha, London, Paris and Philadelphia, see the catalogue entry by <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/18/vers/59?handschrift=1366">Marcus Fraser about Qatar National Library HC.MS.03190</ref>.  </p>
